- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is likely because the paper deals with type theory and inductive types, which are foundational concepts in computer science and logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely because the paper discusses the implementation of inductive types and their use in defining higher inductive types, which are relevant to programming language design. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility because the paper deals with the construction of a model of homotopy type theory, which has connections to information theory through the study of information transfer and communication. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility because the paper discusses the implementation of inductive types, which are a fundamental data structure in computer science. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is a possibility because the paper discusses the implementation of a computational model of homotopy type theory, which involves mathematical concepts and requires software implementation.
